+## Flow 2: Chat Query
+1. User types question (optionally attaches image) â†’ sends to /api/chat
+2. LangGraph agent receives query â†’ classifies intent
+3. Agent selects tool(s): KB Retrieval, Web Search, and/or Code Execution
+4. If KB Retrieval: hybrid BM25 + semantic search â†’ re-rank â†’ top-k chunks
+5. LLM generates grounded answer with citations â†’ streams via SSE
+6. Frontend renders tokens as they arrive + citation links
+
+## Flow 3: MCP Client Query
+1. External client (Cursor/Claude) connects to MCP Server
+2. Client lists available tools (retrieval, search, code_exec)
+3. Client invokes tool with parameters â†’ MCP Server routes to backend service
+4. Results returned via MCP protocol
